{
  "texts": [
    "By mining large datasets that include chemical descriptors, recipe data, and sensory ratings, AI algorithms can propose novel ingredient combinations.",
    "These combinations are often unconventional and may not be easily discovered through traditional sensory panel testing.",
    "In parallel, preference prediction systems use hedonic ratings, behavioral data, and consumption history to generate personalized flavor profiles.",
    "This helps tailor products for specific regional markets or consumer subgroups, enhancing market relevance and satisfaction.",
    "As AI systems are increasingly used to predict consumer preferences and develop personalized products, concerns have emerged regarding potential algorithmic bias, especially when models are trained on datasets that underrepresent certain cultural or regional populations."
  ]
}